<section class="about-section about-section--alt">
  <div class="about-section-inner">
  <p class="about-intro">From the moment you step onboard, the yacht feels less like a vessel — and more like a private villa at sea. Expansive windows flood the interior with natural light, while the open salon and welcoming dining area create a setting designed for connection, celebration, and relaxation. Whether cruising the coastline of South Florida, exploring the Florida Keys, or planning a Bahamas escape, every journey is defined by comfort and capability.</p>
  <h2 class="section-heading">Designed for Comfort, Built for Experience</h2>

  <div class="about-subsection">
    <h3 class="about-subheading">A Bright, Spacious Interior</h3>
    <p>The salon’s sleek hi-lo television system allows for movie nights or game-day viewing on the water, while beautifully finished interiors reflect Azimut’s signature craftsmanship. The layout encourages effortless flow between lounging, dining, and entertaining.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="about-subsection">
    <h3 class="about-subheading">True Overnight Luxury</h3>
    <p>With four well-appointed staterooms accommodating up to eight overnight guests, extended cruising feels indulgent rather than confined. The thoughtful layout offers privacy, comfort, and the freedom to turn a day charter into a memorable multi-day escape.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="about-subsection">
    <h3 class="about-subheading">Outdoor Living at Its Finest</h3>
    <p>The expansive flybridge and bow lounge offer multiple areas for sunbathing, shaded relaxation, dining, and socializing. Guests can spread out comfortably, enjoying South Florida’s sunshine or evening coastal breezes in total comfort.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="about-subsection">
    <h3 class="about-subheading">Smooth, Confident Cruising</h3>
    <p>Powered by twin MAN 850 HP diesel engines and designed with Azimut’s Dual Mode hull, Knot Caught Slippin delivers smooth performance across varying sea conditions. Cruising at speeds up to 24 knots, she is equally suited for relaxed coastal cruising or ambitious island hopping.</p>
  </div>
  </div>
</section>

